  "text": "where the constraint on the filters is to avoid scaling ambiguities. Solving for the sparse codes (x j ) J j=1 and the filters (h c ) C c=1 simultaneously in Eq. 8 is a non-convex optimization problem. The alternating-minimization method solves Eq. 8 in two stages: given an initial estimate of the filters, the algorithm alternates between a CSC step to estimate sparse codes (x j ) J j=1 and a dictionary update step to estimate the filters (h c ) C c=1 given the newly-estimated sparse codes [CITATION_1] . In the case of dense (as opposed to convolutional) dictionary, [CITATION_2] shows that the alternating minimization algorithm converges to the true dictionary whenever the dictionary satisfies RIP [CITATION_3] . A. Convolutional Sparse Coding Update Given the filters H, the CSC step is separable over the J examples. We can solve for the j th sparse code x j using the unconstrained form of (P 2 ) given by",
